# Important: reuse, patterns, and where code lives

**Reuse before inventing.** Prefer existing shared UI—`@/components/ui`, `@/features/_common/patterns/`, and established widgets (e.g. `ListView` for tables, drawer primitives below)—and the **same components and layout patterns** as sibling features in the same surface (drawer, page, form). Do **not** grow orchestration files with large inline JSX: **routes, thin descriptors, and layout shells should stay wire-up only**; put **domain-specific UI** next to its feature module (e.g. client drawer body next to `ClientForm`).

**New reusable building blocks** (clickable regions, context strips, row chrome, cards, section labels—anything that could appear in more than one feature) belong in **`@/features/_common/patterns/`** for app-level patterns, or **`@/components/ui`** for generic controls. Add a **colocated Storybook** story; never use a hardcoded `title` in story meta—let the path define the title. Keep component props **generic**; specialize at the call site if needed.

When a pattern becomes the **standard** way to build a part of the app, **add a short entry under the relevant heading** in this file (e.g. entity drawers) so future work stays consistent.

# Storybook

Colocate `*.stories.tsx` with the component; **do not** set a hardcoded `title` in story `meta`—let the file path define the title (see **Important** above).

**Service-backed stories** (widgets that take `services` or a `WithFooService` slice): **do not** build ad-hoc mock objects inside the story file. Import a factory from the matching **`*.mock.ts`** next to the real service (e.g. `createClientService()` from `@/services/io/ClientService/ClientService.mock.ts`). Reuse existing mocks under `src/services/**/**/*.mock.ts` and `src/api/**/**/*.mock.ts` when possible. If no mock exists for that service, **add** `FooService.mock.ts` (or `foo.api.mock.ts` for API-shaped modules) beside the implementation and export `createFooService()` returning a full implementation of the interface. **Presentational-only** stories (no `services` prop) do not need service mocks.

# Commit messages

Use conventional commits. make subject short and explain the purpose (why's). If the topic really really requires clarifiaction provide short body, ideally max one sentence / 100char.
Do not include the body if the topic is clear.

For few files change, please avoid body, just headline


# Database migration files
**Schema-agnostic SQL (critical):** Do **not** qualify objects with a hardcoded schema (e.g. `public.table`). Use unqualified names (`table`, `policy … ON table`) so migrations follow the session `search_path` and work across environments that do not use `public` or use multiple schemas. Never write `public.` in new migrations; Same idea for `auth.uid()` etc.—use Supabase-provided schemas only where required (`auth`, `storage`), not `public` for app tables.

When you have several related unstaged migrations (e.g. table + policies), merge them into one migration file.

# Preferences / persisted state
Use PreferenceService for any localStorage-backed setting: define a type, zod schema, createLocalStorageApi(key, parse, defaultValue), and expose only get/set (read/write). Keep business logic (e.g. "should we skip?") in the consumer (hook/component), not in the preference service.
Use Zod to parse stored JSON (safeParse); avoid manual type guards.

# Async actions in UI
Use promiseState.useMutation for submit/save/delete: no manual isSaving state or .then()/.catch(); use mutation.track(...) and mt.isInProgress(mutation.state) for disabled/loading. Disable submit button while in progress to avoid double-submit.

# Forms
Use react-hook-form so Enter submits: wrap inputs in <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(...)}>, use form.register(), and type="submit" on the button. Extract form + validation into a subwidget when it has clear boundaries and is reused or makes the parent simpler.

# Schema and API boundaries
Put schema and types next to the API that owns them (e.g. budget target log entry schema in iteration-trigger API, not project-iteration). Use Zod for parsing HTTP/storage payloads; expose a single domain type (e.g. BudgetTargetLogEntry) from the API layer.

# Dead code and unused options
Remove unused exports, components, and parameters (e.g. a component never imported, or a param always passed false). Prefer deleting over commenting out.

# Avoid hardcoded lists when data-driven is possible
Don't hardcode currency lists or similar; derive from actual data (e.g. iteration currencies) and use on-demand loading (e.g. ensureExchange) for the rest when you don't have the full set up front.

# List views (tables)
For tabular lists of domain data (loading/error states, sortable columns, consistent table chrome), use `@/features/_common/ListView.tsx` with `@tanstack/react-table` column definitions (`createColumnHelper`). Put `meta.sortKey` on headers that should sort; the list query type must satisfy `SortableQueryBase` (include `WithSorter` + `WithPagination`, wire `query` / `onQueryChange`, and apply sort in the API or data layer). Avoid ad-hoc `<Table>` + manual skeleton/error blocks when `ListView` already covers that flow.

# Entity drawers (stack) and shared layout
Entity detail drawers use `EntityDrawerRouteLayout` + `EntityDetailDrawers` + per-entity `DrawerDescriptor` implementations under `@/features/_common/drawers/descriptors/`. **Edit flows belong on the stack** (e.g. `billing-form`, `client-form`): `pushEntityDrawer` from header actions, dedicated `*FormSpec` + `*FormDrawerDescriptor`, `popEntityDrawer` on save/cancel—**not** `InlinePopoverForm` in the drawer header.

**New stack entity types** (`client`, `workspace`, `*-form`, etc.): extend `EntityStackItem` and **every** branch in `getEntityStackKey` + `entityDrawerDescriptor` (`getLabel`, `getTitle`, `renderBreadcrumbLabel`, `renderSmallPreview`, `renderDrawerContent`, `renderHeaderActions`). Update `EntityDetailDrawers` for `isFormStackEntity`, `usesBulkCostDrawerShell` (flex body + `DrawerFooter` pattern like `BulkCreateCostDrawer`), and `drawerDescriptionForEntity` when the new type is a form or needs a visible description. Export descriptors from `descriptors/index.ts` as needed.

**Environment management pages** (sidebar **Environment** → list + drawer, e.g. **Clients**, **Workspaces**): use **top-level** routes via `myRouting.forGlobal().manageClients()` (`/configuration/clients`) and `myRouting.forGlobal().manageWorkspaces()` (`/configuration/workspaces`)—not under `/w/:workspaceId/clients/:clientId/...`. Workspace/client **scope** for breadcrumbs, `EntityDrawerRouteLayout`, and filters comes from **`LocationService`**: URL when on a nested `/w/.../clients/...` route, otherwise **sessionStorage** last scope (updated whenever scope is read from the URL), else **`idSpecUtils.ofAll()`**. **Workspace/client switchers** on those pages call `tryPersistCurrentRoute`, which must **stay on** `/clients` or `/workspaces` and refresh stored scope (see `LocationService.impl`). Add **singleton** entries in `createPersistentBrowserHistory.connected` (`scopeParamNames: []`, fixed storage key) for list query persistence. In `RootWidget`, wrap the page in `EntityDrawerRouteLayout`; optional **`<Navigate replace>`** from legacy `/w/:workspaceId/clients/:clientId/environment/{clients|workspaces}` to the new paths. Implement `*ManageWidget` under `features/<domain>/` with `CommonPageContainer`, workspace + client breadcrumbs + `BreadcrumbPage`, debounced search via `useDebouncedUrlSyncedSearch` and `queryParamsService.forEntity("<key>")`, and `ListView` with `onRowClick` → `openEntityDrawer({ type: "<entity>", id })`. Register the list query type and zod parser on **`FrontServices`** and **`services.connected`**. Domain `*Query` must satisfy **List views**. Colocate drawer UI and stack form in that feature folder; keep routes and descriptors thin.

**Building blocks** for drawer bodies and previews (see **Important** above): `DrawerMainInfoGrid` (header preview), `PanelSectionLabel` + `SurfaceCard` + `Separator` (sections), `MutedInsetRow` (inset list rows), `DrawerContextEntityStrip` (workspace + client when nesting to another entity). For file/image uploads, compose **`UploadDropCard`** + **`FileDropEmptyState`** (empty) + **`SelectedUploadCard`** (chosen file or logo preview), as in AI billing payment matcher and client logo.

**Mutations + RLS** for editable domain rows surfaced on these pages: extend `MutationApi` / HTTP implementation, `MutationService.impl`, and mocks; add Supabase **policies or RPCs** as required (e.g. member-scoped `UPDATE`). Prefer invalidating relevant React Query keys via existing `messageService.reportSystemEffect` flows where already wired (e.g. workspace lists).
